snippet: Emergency workers summoned to a shooting scene in Richmond Hill, Queens, pronounced a woman dead, but the police later heard sounds coming from her.
abstract: New York City police reveal that woman deemed dead by emergency medical workers, responding to shooting in Queens, was in fact alive, and was taken to hospital in critical condition; woman, whose name has not been released, appears to have shot herself.
lead_paragraph: Emergency workers summoned to a shooting scene in Richmond Hill, Queens, pronounced a woman dead, but the police later heard sounds coming from her.

headline.main: Woman Called Dead Is Found to Still Be Alive
headline.print_headline: Woman Called Dead Is Found to Still Be Alive
